id "1375984c-09be-4a53-a5be-fb6a852a6b55")) (text "iPod 1.8in 50-pin IDE  <->  CompactFlash True-IDE  UDMA BRIDGE  (MachXO2 LCMXO2-2000HC-TG100)" (exclude_from_sim no) (at 40 12 0) (effects (font (size 3.5 3.5) (bold yes)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid "f037d868-2db2-4f3f-b8a8-06495e1bb725")) (text "UDMA / CRC: U1 (MachXO2) actively re-times the bus and is the device the iPod talks to. The FPGA HDL terminates the host UDMA burst, and on writes may IGNORE / force-OK the host-supplied CRC while regenerating a correct CRC toward the CF card. A purely passive adapter CANNOT do this - that is why an FPGA sits in the datapath." (exclude_from_sim no) (at 40 245 0) (effects (font (size 2 2)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid "5b8b5b4a-98ca-4dc0-a759-5433705dbdd9")) (text "VERIFY: J1 pin map follows the standard Toshiba 1.8in / CF True-IDE 50-pin order. Confirm pin-1 reference & orientation against the interposer (HXSP-09CF69) before fab." (exclude_from_sim no) (at 40 252 0) (effects (font (size 2 2)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid "b0471423-e029-4ad5-b736-acfc27f5af1d")) (text "PROG: MachXO2 has internal config flash (instant-on). Program over J3 JTAG header (TCK/TMS/TDI/TDO + PROGRAMN/DONE) with a Lattice/FTDI programmer (Diamond Programmer / openFPGALoader). Single 3.3V rail, bus-powered from host (J1.13/38). I/O pin assignment is a starting point - lock final pins in Diamond (.lpf)." (exclude_from_sim no) (at 40 259 0) (effects (font (size 2 2)) (justify left bottom)) (uuid "6583ef09-af3c-474c-b5e4-8d005fa1f07e")) (symbol (lib_id "ipcf:LCMXO2-2000HC-TG100_BRIDGE") (at 150 112 0.0) (unit 1) (in_bom yes) (on_board yes) (dnp no) (uuid "f737882c-29a7-4c0f-a521-8184506900c4") (property "Reference" "U1" (at 150 109.46 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)))) (property "Value" "LCMXO2-2000HC-4TG100C" (at 150 114.54 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)))) (property "Footprint" "Package_QFP:TQFP-100_14x14mm_P0.5mm" (at 150 112 0) (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (hide yes))) (property "MPN" "